Police are looking for suspects involved in the murder of two ANC members in Nelson Mandela Bay. Ward 43 councillor Andile Andries and branch secretary Lubabalo Keso were gunned down by unknown men while leaving Andries’s home. ANC Eastern Cape's Loyiso Magqashela has more. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC in the Eastern Cape is calling for calm after two Nelson Mandela Bay members were killed on Monday. The two murders come after another ANC councillor Zwelandile Booi was gunned down in February. READ: Manhunt for killers of ANC NMB members On Monday, ANC Nelson Mandela Bay Ward councillor Andile Andries and the regional executive committee member Lubabalo Keso were shot dead outside Andries' home. The ANC's Luyolo Nqakula said this was an act of plain criminality. "We are calling for calm from all our members," said Nqakula. 